The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Friday, April 09, 2004 				 Secy at Naidus service
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENTNew Delhi, April 8: Defence minister George Fernandes personal secretary was seen on the platform from where the manifesto of the National Democratic Alliance was released  an attendance that can invite censure under the model of conduct.																								Fernandes secretary Ashok Subrahmanian was hovering on the stage today as the coalition made public its manifesto. But the official defended himself, saying: We are fully aware of the model code of conduct. But we are not there for campaigning. We are there to assist the media, receive phone calls, fix appointments.																								Defending his presence on the stage  a violation of the model code  the secretary said: I had to go on stage to give some medicine to (BJP chief) M. Venkaiah Naidu.																								The model code of conduct says: Ministers shall not combine their official visit with electioneering work and shall not also make use of official machinery or personnel during electioneering work.																								Under the previous chief election commissioner, J.M. Lyngdoh, the poll panel had stuck meticulously to the code of conduct. 																								During Decembers Assembly elections, the commission ordered the Chhattisgarh government to transfer two district collectors for violating the code of conduct.																								Sources said the poll panel is less proactive now, waiting instead for a party to make a formal complaint before issuing an order.																								At todays function, Prime Minister Atal Bihari Vajpayee was accompanied by his personal secretary Ajay Bisaria  but this does not violate the model code as the guidelines make an exception for the Prime Minister and President. 
